## Research Experience

National Science Foundation Graduate Research Fellow, University of Washington. September 2021-present.  
Advisor: E.V. Armbrust  
Examining the trophic capabilities of protists across large-scale ocean gradients compared to physio-chemical factors through large-scale bioinformatic data analyses, as well as field and culture experiments.  

Senior Research Support Associate, MIT. January 2019 – August 2021.  
Advisor: S.W. Chisholm  
Carried out bioinformatic analyses for numerous projects including 16S-based identification of heterotrophs present in picocyanobacteria enrichment cultures — analysis of RNA, methylation, and genomic sequencing from dark-adapted Prochlorococcus — and identification of signatures and regulation of novel integrative elements in Prochlorococcus.  

Research Assistant, Carleton College. January - November 2018.  
Advisor: Rika Anderson  
Analyzed hydrothermal vent metagenomes to characterize viral community structure — mined CRISPR loci to build virus-host interaction networks — and collected hydrothermal vent viral metagenomes during 2018 Lost City Expedition.  

REU Student, Eco-Informatics Summer Institute, Oregon State University. June - August 2017.  
Advisors: Julia Jones and Rebecca Hutchinson  
Analyzed diversity of plant and pollinator communities across long timeseries of alpine meadows of the Western Cascades.  

Intern, Monarch Lab, University of Minnesota. November - December 2017.  
Conducted literature review of anthropogenic contributions to monarch butterfly habitat loss.  

